  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.15.0\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nUsing `helpers.reset(ROC_URL, block_height)` gives me the following error: `A withdrawalsRoot for a header can only be provided with EIP4895 being activated`.\r\n\r\nThis only happens for some block_heights like `17394208`, `17364206` or `17274264` for example. Usually around and after the shanghai upgrade.\r\n\r\nAs soon as I get the error, my fork seems to be broken and I can't reset to block heights before shanghai or any block heights to be exact.  \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\nInit fork at block height `17394208` using `helpers.reset` or by sending `hardhat_reset` to fork. \r\n\r\nTry to reset to any block height.\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\nEIP 4895 withdrawalsRoot hardhat_reset helpers.reset",
